39
0:02:05.552,000 --> 0:02:06,000
that people can't even guess at,

40
0:02:07.477,000 --> 0:02:1,000
like seaweed and other things that are scary.

41
0:02:11.458,000 --> 0:02:13,000
But, when it comes to writing,

42
0:02:13.709,000 --> 0:02:16,000
the thing that I've been sort of thinking about lately, and wondering about lately,

43
0:02:17.693,000 --> 0:02:18,000
is why?

44
0:02:18.867,000 --> 0:02:19,000
You know, is it rational?

45
0:02:20.161,000 --> 0:02:22,000
Is it logical that anybody should be expected

46
0:02:22.408,000 --> 0:02:26,000
to be afraid of the work that they feel they were put on this Earth to do.

47
0:02:27.06,000 --> 0:02:31,000
And what is it specifically about creative ventures

48
0:02:31.46,000 --> 0:02:34,000
that seems to make us really nervous about each other's mental health

49
0:02:34.932,000 --> 0:02:37,000
in a way that other careers kind of don't do, you know?

50
0:02:37.959,000 --> 0:02:4,000
